properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 18 at 1:24AM MST until January 18 at 10:00AM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills. Wind chills as low as 25 to 30
below zero.

* WHERE...Butte County, the Northern Meade County Plains and
Ziebach County.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM MST this morning.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed
skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
A wind chill advisory means the combination of wind and cold
temperatures will create dangerously low wind chill values. If
you go outside, cover all parts of your body, especially your
head, face, and hands.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM MST THIS MORNING
